<HEAD>$55 Million Lotto Winner Starts Foundation For Needy</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TALLAHASSEE, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The winner of the nation's single
biggest lottery jackpot has formed a foundation to help the needy
with some of her $55.1 million.
   ``It's a dream I want to live on long after I'm gone,'' Sheelah
Ryan said Thursday in announcing the formation of the private,
non-profit Ryan Foundation.
   Ms. Ryan, 63, of Winter Springs, said the foundation will provide
shelter for the homeless, help the elderly, feed the hungry and
protect abused women and children.
   The former real estate saleswoman won the jackpot in September.
Although other jackpots since then have exceeded $55.1 million, they
have been split among multiple winners.
   Ms. Ryan said she kicked off her foundation with ``a substantial
sum'' of her winnings.
