<SECOND>AM-BRF--Copter Crash,0121</SECOND>
<HEAD>Three Missing After Helicopter Crashes In Sea</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HELSINKI, Finland (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A helicopter crashed into the sea off
southern Finland, and three people were missing, the coast guard
reported.
   The Agusta Bell 206 Jet Ranger crashed Thursday night shortly
after taking off from the submarine support ship Skat near Kokar
island, about 125 miles west of Helsinki.
   The ship's crew launched a search in boats, but found only parts
of the helicopter.
   In addition to the pilot, the helicopter was carrying a shipyard
worker and a British researcher.
   The coast guard said there was almost no chance of survivors from
the crash in the icy water. The cause of the accident was not known.
