alleged beating Wednesday, and was transferred to St. Christopher's
Hospital for Children, where he was in good condition Friday,
officials said.
   The beating occurred after the boy returned from a day of washing
cars for tips in the neighborhood with $11 in his pocket, according
to police.
   Miss Oliphant admitted nothing after her arrest, saying the child
had caused the injuries himself, according to police.
