<SECOND>PM-Car of Year,0161</SECOND>
<HEAD>Motor Trend Names Thunderbird SC Car of Year</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Ford Thunderbird Super Coupe has been named
Motor Trend's Car of the Year for 1989, the first time the
prestigious announcement has been made at a Detroit auto show.
   Selection of the Thunderbird SC on Thursday represents the third
time in the past four years that a Ford has received the Motor Trend
honor.
   The supercharged Thunderbird, which went on sale in December
after months of media exposure, was chosen because it ``offers
everything a personal luxury car buyer could ever want ... speed,
style, comfort, convenience and value,'' the magazine said in its
February issue.
   The car is built at Ford's Lorain, Ohio, assembly plant beside
the Mercury Cougar.
   The magazine's 1986 car of the year was the Ford Taurus, and in
1987, it was the Thunderbird Turbo Coupe. Last year, the award went
to the Pontiac Grand Prix.
