<HEAD>Northwest Cuts Lowest Fares for Limited Period</HEAD>
<DATELINE>EAGAN, Minn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Northwest Airlines said Friday it has cut as
much as $50 off its lowest fares between Minneapolis-St. Paul and 19
U.S. destinations for a limited period.
   Tickets can be purchased at sale prices anytime through Jan. 31
for travel to be completed by midnight Feb. 28, said Jim McKeon,
district sales manager.
   To qualify for the lowest fares, passengers may fly anytime
during off-peak hours, which are noon Mondays through noon Thursdays
or noon Saturdays to noon Sundays.
   Northwest also reduced peak period discount fares for travel
during the remainder of the week. Seats, which are limited, must be
reserved at least seven days before travel, and passengers must stay
at their destinations over a Saturday night. Tickets are not
refundable.
   As examples of the savings, McKeon said roundtrip tickets to San
Antonio, Texas, are now available for $208, $50 off the lowest
discount fare. Seats to Fort Walton Beach, Fla., are $208 roundtrip,
$50 off the lowest discount, and roundtrip tickets to Austin, Texas,
are reduced by $50 to $208.
   Senior citizens at least 62 years old save an additional 10
percent off the sale fares.
